Tokenization Technique :

Tokenization is the process of breaking down text into smaller units (tokens).

Why we should learn Tokenization in details.

Tokens in LLMs


* Revenue & Cost

    * LLM providers charge based on tokens processed (input + output).
    * More tokens = higher cost.

* Input Format

    * All LLMs convert text into tokens before processing.
    * Tokens are the fundamental building blocks for model understanding.

* Applications (like RAG)

    * Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and other LLM-based apps rely on tokens.
    * Token count determines how much context fits into the model’s window.
    * Efficient tokenization = more meaningful content packed into the same context size.


